title: PHOTOS: Queen Elizabeth II meeting with every US president since she began her reign
text:
Queen Elizabeth II marked an unprecedented 65 years on the British throne Monday. On her sapphire jubilee, here are photos of her meeting with every U.S. president since she began her reign. 
AP Photo The queen, as Princess Elizabeth, with President Harry Truman at the Canadian Embassy in Washington, Nov. 1, 1951.
AP Photo   Queen Elizabeth at Balmoral Castle with President Dwight Eisenhower, Prince Philip, Princess Anne and Prince Charles, Aug. 29, 1959.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President John F. Kennedy, first lady Jackie Kennedy and Prince Philip before a state dinner at Buckingham Palace, June 5, 1961.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President Richard Nixon and British Prime Minister Edward Heath at Chequers, Buckinghamshire, in 1970.*
Also from the Washington Examiner DOJ files brief defending Trump's refugee ban The amicus brief was filed on Monday evening.
By Anna Giaritelli â€¢ 02/06/17 6:28 PM AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President Gerald Ford and first lady Betty Ford, waving from the balcony of the White House, July 7, 1976.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President Jimmy Carter at Buckingham Palace in May 1977.
AP Photo Also from the Washington Examiner Congress investigating Secret Service agent who suggested she wouldn't take 'a bullet' for Trump Lawmakers did not specifically mention the Secret Service's own investigation into O'Grady's Facebook post.
  6:27 PM Queen Elizabeth horseback riding with President Ronald Reagan on the grounds of Windsor Castle, June 8, 1982.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with Ronald and Nancy Reagan at Buckingham Palace, several months after they left the White House, June 14, 1989.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President George H.W. Bush, first lady Barbara Bush and Prince Philip at a dinner hosted by the queen at the British Embassy in Washington, May 16, 1991.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth speaks during a dinner with President Bill Clinton, June, 4, 1994, to commemorate the 50th anniversary of D-Day.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President Bill Clinton, first lady Hillary Clinton and Prince Philip at Buckingham Palace, Nov. 29 1995.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth toasts with President George W. Bush during a State Dinner at the White House, May 7, 2007.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth and Prince Philip with President George W. Bush, first lady Laura Bush, former President George H.W. Bush and former first lady Barbara Bush before the start of a dinner at the British Embassy in Washington, May 8, 2007.
AP Photo Queen Elizabeth with President Barack Obama , first lady Michelle Obama and Prince Philip before a dinner hosted by the queen at Buckingham Palace, May 24, 2011.
The queen has not yet met with President Trump . 
*Queen Elizabeth did not meet with Lyndon Johnson during his presidency.
